[APPLAUSE]

00:00:38.550 --> 00:00:39.500
JESSICA BIEL: Hello.

00:00:39.500 --> 00:00:40.660
ALAN SEALES: Yeah, so
please welcome to the stage

00:00:40.660 --> 00:00:41.430
Jessica Biel.

00:00:41.430 --> 00:00:42.579
JESSICA BIEL: Hello.

00:00:42.579 --> 00:00:43.620
ALAN SEALES: Have a seat.

00:00:43.620 --> 00:00:44.328
JESSICA BIEL: Hi.

00:00:46.600 --> 00:00:49.090
ALAN SEALES: And we just
watched episode one,

00:00:49.090 --> 00:00:50.660
everyone who's here.

00:00:50.660 --> 00:00:55.920
I want to quickly touch on
the actual murder scene,

00:00:55.920 --> 00:00:58.459
because I saw the whole
audience squirm and--

00:00:58.459 --> 00:00:59.250
JESSICA BIEL: Good.

00:00:59.250 --> 00:01:02.270
ALAN SEALES: --bite their nails
and do all sorts of things.

00:01:02.270 --> 00:01:06.099
Is that the normal reaction
that you get from us?

00:01:06.099 --> 00:01:06.890
JESSICA BIEL: Yeah.

00:01:06.890 --> 00:01:11.600
I actually haven't watched the
show with many big audiences

00:01:11.600 --> 00:01:12.427
before.

00:01:12.427 --> 00:01:13.260
ALAN SEALES: Really?

00:01:13.260 --> 00:01:15.960
JESSICA BIEL: Well
it's rare, I think,

00:01:15.960 --> 00:01:18.490
to have a television show that
you get to screen like this.

00:01:18.490 --> 00:01:20.330
It's new.

00:01:20.330 --> 00:01:22.430
Just went to the Tribeca
Film Fest last year,

00:01:22.430 --> 00:01:23.610
but that's a new thing.

00:01:23.610 --> 00:01:25.340
Usually you're
bringing films there.

00:01:25.340 --> 00:01:27.760
You're not usually
bringing shows there.

00:01:27.760 --> 00:01:30.490
So I haven't seen this
more than a few times

00:01:30.490 --> 00:01:32.550
with a larger crowd.

00:01:32.550 --> 00:01:36.350
But yes, it's always a
bit of a cringe moment

00:01:36.350 --> 00:01:39.050
because it comes out of nowhere,
which is the idea, right,

00:01:39.050 --> 00:01:41.930
is the idea that
this person is just

00:01:41.930 --> 00:01:49.460
kind of blacking and having
this sort of attack almost.

00:01:49.460 --> 00:01:50.860
And yeah, everybody cringes.

00:01:50.860 --> 00:01:53.270
And it's over really
fast, which is

00:01:53.270 --> 00:01:55.850
kind of another part
of the whole idea

00:01:55.850 --> 00:01:58.640
that when violence
occurs in life,

00:01:58.640 --> 00:02:03.220
it doesn't always have this
long, dramatic experience.

00:02:03.220 --> 00:02:05.330
It's like boom and it's
done, and no one even

00:02:05.330 --> 00:02:06.510
knows what's happened.

00:02:06.510 --> 00:02:09.090
ALAN SEALES: So
what was the impetus

00:02:09.090 --> 00:02:10.662
to screen it at festivals?

00:02:10.662 --> 00:02:12.370
Because you said it's
a new thing, right?

00:02:12.370 --> 00:02:13.315
JESSICA BIEL: Well
for the festival

00:02:13.315 --> 00:02:14.600
it's a new thing I mean.

00:02:14.600 --> 00:02:17.990
To I think only last--

00:02:17.990 --> 00:02:20.410
sorry, the year we were,
which is last year,

00:02:20.410 --> 00:02:22.330
so the year before
that, I feel like that's

00:02:22.330 --> 00:02:25.870
the first time that the Tribeca
Film Festival started screening

00:02:25.870 --> 00:02:27.260
shows.

00:02:27.260 --> 00:02:29.620
So for the film
festivals I believe

00:02:29.620 --> 00:02:30.720
it's kind of a new thing.

00:02:30.720 --> 00:02:32.579
So when you're doing
a TV show and then you

00:02:32.579 --> 00:02:34.370
get to go to a film
festival, first of all,

00:02:34.370 --> 00:02:36.939
it's kind of surprising
and exciting.

00:02:36.939 --> 00:02:39.480
And then you go and you see the
show that you've been making,

00:02:39.480 --> 00:02:42.220
but you've never expected
to see it on a huge screen.

00:02:42.220 --> 00:02:45.001
You expect it to
just be on TV, small.

00:02:45.001 --> 00:02:46.500
ALAN SEALES: These
are just big TVs.

00:02:46.500 --> 00:02:49.050
JESSICA BIEL: I know,
But it's different.

00:02:49.050 --> 00:02:51.820
It just seems different somehow.

00:02:51.820 --> 00:02:54.290
ALAN SEALES: Does that mean
that you filmed the pilot

00:02:54.290 --> 00:02:56.610
a long time ago and then
you just picked up two

00:02:56.610 --> 00:02:58.060
through eight recently?

00:02:58.060 --> 00:02:59.870
JESSICA BIEL: Yeah,
not too long ago.

00:02:59.870 --> 00:03:03.732
We filmed it in the fall.

00:03:03.732 --> 00:03:06.680
I think it was the fall.

00:03:06.680 --> 00:03:08.860
ALAN SEALES: I guess what
I'm asking is normally you

00:03:08.860 --> 00:03:10.492
film a pilot, it gets greenlit.

00:03:10.492 --> 00:03:11.950
You have to screen
it and what not,

00:03:11.950 --> 00:03:12.850
see if there's interest in it.

00:03:12.850 --> 00:03:13.974
It may or may not ever air.

00:03:13.974 --> 00:03:16.690
Did you go into it knowing
you would make the full eight

00:03:16.690 --> 00:03:17.190
episodes?

00:03:17.190 --> 00:03:19.023
JESSICA BIEL: No, we
did what you just said.

00:03:19.023 --> 00:03:22.320
So we developed the material.

00:03:22.320 --> 00:03:26.490
We got a writer on
board, Derek Simonds,

00:03:26.490 --> 00:03:28.010
who then wrote
the pilot and what

00:03:28.010 --> 00:03:32.170
the bible for what the
show would look like.

00:03:32.170 --> 00:03:34.090
Not necessarily how many
episodes it would be,

00:03:34.090 --> 00:03:35.530
because we didn't quite know.

00:03:35.530 --> 00:03:38.440
It can change when
you eventually

00:03:38.440 --> 00:03:39.910
sell it to the right place.

00:03:39.910 --> 00:03:45.010
And they have a lot of opinions
about, is it eight, is it ten,

00:03:45.010 --> 00:03:49.910
is it only like a two hour
thing two nights in a row?

00:03:49.910 --> 00:03:56.250
So we wrote the pilot, and
then we pitched it around.

00:03:56.250 --> 00:04:00.780
And USA was interested.

00:04:00.780 --> 00:04:06.150
And so basically that's
when they bought--

00:04:06.150 --> 00:04:09.629
sorry, so then they gave us
the money to film the pilot.

00:04:09.629 --> 00:04:10.920
ALAN SEALES: Money's important.

00:04:10.920 --> 00:04:12.140
JESSICA BIEL: That's
what we needed, right?

00:04:12.140 --> 00:04:13.770
Money's important sometimes.

00:04:13.770 --> 00:04:16.290
And then we showed
them the pilot.

00:04:16.290 --> 00:04:18.260
And then they picked up
the rest of the season.

00:04:18.260 --> 00:04:21.839
So it's possible we would
have just shot the pilot

00:04:21.839 --> 00:04:24.982
and no one ever saw it again.

00:04:24.982 --> 00:04:26.440
ALAN SEALES: Because
I was reading,

00:04:26.440 --> 00:04:29.030
two through eight-- this is an
eight part miniseries for those

00:04:29.030 --> 00:04:33.060
of you who don't figure out what
I'm talking about are ready.

00:04:33.060 --> 00:04:34.310
You know what the end will be.

00:04:34.310 --> 00:04:37.610
You know you're not going
to a season two, right?

00:04:37.610 --> 00:04:39.140
JESSICA BIEL: No,
not necessarily.

00:04:39.140 --> 00:04:40.550
ALAN SEALES: Ooh.

00:04:40.550 --> 00:04:42.370
[LAUGHTER]

00:04:42.370 --> 00:04:45.190
JESSICA BIEL: I mean,
television is so cool.

00:04:45.190 --> 00:04:47.885
The idea was sort of it
could be anthology series.

00:04:52.000 --> 00:04:56.960
What we want to do with season
one is we will close the case.

00:04:56.960 --> 00:05:00.790
So you're not going to
be season two going, ugh,

00:05:00.790 --> 00:05:03.010
I still have to wait
to get the answer.

00:05:03.010 --> 00:05:04.510
We're going to
close out this case

00:05:04.510 --> 00:05:05.710
and you're going to
understand what happened.

00:05:05.710 --> 00:05:07.376
We're going to give
you all the answers.

00:05:07.376 --> 00:05:11.360
Season two, if Bill
is interested--

00:05:11.360 --> 00:05:14.130
Bill Pullman I'm talking
about obviously--

00:05:14.130 --> 00:05:17.780
he can take on a new case.

00:05:17.780 --> 00:05:20.750
And I don't want to give away
what the ending's going to be,

00:05:20.750 --> 00:05:23.560
but there is a possibility
that maybe my character

00:05:23.560 --> 00:05:26.930
could be involved in some way.

00:05:26.930 --> 00:05:29.832
But I don't think that's really
giving away much, necessarily.

00:05:29.832 --> 00:05:32.290
ALAN SEALES: But we know that
you're involved in this case.

00:05:32.290 --> 00:05:33.665
JESSICA BIEL: Yes,
I'm definitely

00:05:33.665 --> 00:05:35.290
involved in this case.

00:05:35.290 --> 00:05:38.689
Or you could recast
the whole thing.

00:05:38.689 --> 00:05:39.980
ALAN SEALES: "True Detectives."

00:05:39.980 --> 00:05:41.980
JESSICA BIEL: Right, or
"American Horror Story,"

00:05:41.980 --> 00:05:45.512
or put characters
in other positions.

00:05:45.512 --> 00:05:46.720
You could do a lot of things.

00:05:46.720 --> 00:05:48.970
ALAN SEALES: Yeah, and you
would be interested in that

00:05:48.970 --> 00:05:50.690
from the executive
producer standpoint--

00:05:50.690 --> 00:05:51.420
JESSICA BIEL: Well yeah.

00:05:51.420 --> 00:05:53.330
ALAN SEALES: --not from
the acting standpoint.

00:05:53.330 --> 00:05:54.580
JESSICA BIEL: Well
from both, bu yeah,

00:05:54.580 --> 00:05:56.538
definitely from the
producer standpoint I would

00:05:56.538 --> 00:06:00.190
love my actors to come back.

00:06:00.190 --> 00:06:02.790
ALAN SEALES: So is this the
first time you've executive

00:06:02.790 --> 00:06:05.480
produced anything or is
this old hat for you?

00:06:05.480 --> 00:06:09.830
JESSICA BIEL: Well I produced a
film with my producing partner

00:06:09.830 --> 00:06:12.380
Michelle Purple and my
small little tiny company

00:06:12.380 --> 00:06:17.490
called Iron Ocean just this past
year called "The Book of Love."

00:06:17.490 --> 00:06:20.510
We produced a small short film.

00:06:20.510 --> 00:06:24.150
So this is my first
television producing.

00:06:24.150 --> 00:06:26.800
ALAN SEALES: And how is it
different for you starring

00:06:26.800 --> 00:06:28.482
in it and producing it?

00:06:28.482 --> 00:06:30.940
JESSICA BIEL: Well it's just
kind of double duty, you know?

00:06:30.940 --> 00:06:33.800
I have to wear a couple of hats.

00:06:33.800 --> 00:06:37.580
But definitely when
I'm working on set,

00:06:37.580 --> 00:06:39.280
on the days I'm
working on set, we

00:06:39.280 --> 00:06:41.420
have a really good
team around us.

00:06:41.420 --> 00:06:44.240
Like I mentioned before, my
producing partner Michelle

00:06:44.240 --> 00:06:47.569
and Charlie Gogolak, another
one of our producers,

00:06:47.569 --> 00:06:48.860
there's a lot of support there.

00:06:48.860 --> 00:06:52.450
So they're kind of managing the
day to day producorial stuff.

00:06:52.450 --> 00:06:55.279
And I can kind of focus
on the creative stuff.

00:06:55.279 --> 00:06:56.320
ALAN SEALES: Producorial.

00:06:56.320 --> 00:06:57.020
JESSICA BIEL: Producorial.

00:06:57.020 --> 00:06:57.950
ALAN SEALES: I like that.

00:06:57.950 --> 00:06:59.200
JESSICA BIEL: It's a hard job.

00:06:59.200 --> 00:07:02.160
I'm not great at it.

00:07:02.160 --> 00:07:06.700
I'm very good and I like
the creative producing.

00:07:06.700 --> 00:07:07.850
I want to talk to writers.

00:07:07.850 --> 00:07:09.130
I want to talk to actors.

00:07:09.130 --> 00:07:13.470
I want to character develop,
story arc, character arc.

00:07:13.470 --> 00:07:15.440
I want to do that
kind of producing.

00:07:15.440 --> 00:07:17.911
And my partner has to do
all the horrible stuff.

00:07:17.911 --> 00:07:19.660
ALAN SEALES: Well it
seems like the best--

00:07:19.660 --> 00:07:20.640
JESSICA BIEL: It
works out for me.

00:07:20.640 --> 00:07:22.973
ALAN SEALES: --you've got the
best of both worlds, yeah.

00:07:24.730 --> 00:07:27.277
I'm going to quote
you for a second.

00:07:27.277 --> 00:07:29.360
You said, "I've never
gotten a new romantic comedy

00:07:29.360 --> 00:07:30.320
like most of the girls.

00:07:30.320 --> 00:07:33.520
Maybe because I'm fit people
assume I'm not funny."

00:07:33.520 --> 00:07:34.860
JESSICA BIEL: I said that?

00:07:34.860 --> 00:07:35.430
ALAN SEALES: That's what--

00:07:35.430 --> 00:07:36.000
JESSICA BIEL: I don't
think I said that.

00:07:36.000 --> 00:07:36.710
ALAN SEALES: That's
what the internet said.

00:07:36.710 --> 00:07:37.040
I googled it.

00:07:37.040 --> 00:07:38.230
JESSICA BIEL: Well the
internet is always right.

00:07:38.230 --> 00:07:39.313
ALAN SEALES: I googled it.

00:07:39.313 --> 00:07:39.850
[LAUGHTER]

00:07:39.850 --> 00:07:42.640
JESSICA BIEL: OK
let's go with it.

00:07:42.640 --> 00:07:47.580
I'm fit, therefore
I'm not funny?

00:07:47.580 --> 00:07:49.570
That's what it says?

00:07:49.570 --> 00:07:50.756
No, don't repeat it.

00:07:50.756 --> 00:07:51.256
Please God--

00:07:51.256 --> 00:07:51.756
[APPLAUSE]

00:07:51.756 --> 00:07:53.319
--I beg you.

00:07:53.319 --> 00:07:54.360
Anyway, let's keep going.

00:07:54.360 --> 00:07:55.859
I know where you're
going with this.

00:07:55.859 --> 00:07:58.690
ALAN SEALES: So this is a very
dramatic role, very serious.

00:07:58.690 --> 00:08:01.490
"Chainsaw Massacre,"
"7th Heaven," you

00:08:01.490 --> 00:08:06.260
were in the third "Blade" with
Wesley Snipes, all of these

00:08:06.260 --> 00:08:07.525
are not funny roles.

00:08:07.525 --> 00:08:08.650
JESSICA BIEL: You're right.

00:08:08.650 --> 00:08:11.800
ALAN SEALES: They're not even
air quotes, but funny roles.

00:08:11.800 --> 00:08:13.860
They're actually not funny.

00:08:13.860 --> 00:08:16.454
Do the roles seek you out or
do you seek out the roles?

00:08:16.454 --> 00:08:18.370
JESSICA BIEL: No, this
is a very good question

00:08:18.370 --> 00:08:20.578
because when you put it on
paper like that, I'm like,

00:08:20.578 --> 00:08:21.780
what is wrong with me?

00:08:21.780 --> 00:08:24.465
Why am I want to scare everybody
and be serious all the time?

00:08:24.465 --> 00:08:26.840
Because I'm really not that
serious of a person actually.

00:08:26.840 --> 00:08:27.506
So I don't know.

00:08:27.506 --> 00:08:33.059
I think it must be a little
bit of both, somehow.

00:08:33.059 --> 00:08:35.210
You know what it is?

00:08:35.210 --> 00:08:39.750
I like to be scared, and I
like to watch dramatic thing,

00:08:39.750 --> 00:08:40.250
I think.

00:08:40.250 --> 00:08:41.260
Maybe that's what it is.

00:08:41.260 --> 00:08:45.070
So if there's a cool
piece of material--

00:08:45.070 --> 00:08:47.160
I'm just looking at it
is if it's something

00:08:47.160 --> 00:08:49.050
that I would watch,
and then maybe I would

00:08:49.050 --> 00:08:50.300
want to be in it or something.

00:08:50.300 --> 00:08:51.030
Maybe that's it.

00:08:51.030 --> 00:08:52.750
ALAN SEALES: So you don't
watch anything funny?

00:08:52.750 --> 00:08:54.708
JESSICA BIEL: Well see,
that's not true either.

00:08:54.708 --> 00:08:57.620
I mean, I watch
more dramatic stuff.

00:08:57.620 --> 00:09:00.327
But of course I love to laugh.

00:09:00.327 --> 00:09:02.410
I'm being really insecure
about this about myself.

00:09:02.410 --> 00:09:03.530
[LAUGHTER]

00:09:03.530 --> 00:09:06.330
I need to change
something about my life.

00:09:06.330 --> 00:09:09.110
ALAN SEALES: All right, then I
will co-write a comedy and you

00:09:09.110 --> 00:09:09.610
will--

00:09:09.610 --> 00:09:10.530
JESSICA BIEL: Please.

00:09:10.530 --> 00:09:11.254
Thank you.

00:09:11.254 --> 00:09:12.920
ALAN SEALES: You'll
be first on my list.

00:09:12.920 --> 00:09:14.860
JESSICA BIEL: I hope so.

00:09:14.860 --> 00:09:16.610
ALAN SEALES: So there's
a tie-in obviously

00:09:16.610 --> 00:09:20.139
with the book that is sitting
here with your picture on it.

00:09:20.139 --> 00:09:21.180
Yeah, have you seen this?

00:09:21.180 --> 00:09:21.690
JESSICA BIEL: I have seen that.

00:09:21.690 --> 00:09:22.981
I think that looks pretty cool.

00:09:22.981 --> 00:09:25.320
I never thought I'd be on
the cover of a book before.

00:09:25.320 --> 00:09:27.964
Well I mean, it's a
little random, no?

00:09:27.964 --> 00:09:29.630
ALAN SEALES: Well,
if you exec produce--

00:09:29.630 --> 00:09:29.930
JESSICA BIEL: It's really cool.

00:09:29.930 --> 00:09:32.060
ALAN SEALES: --something
based on a book, yeah.

00:09:32.060 --> 00:09:35.050
JESSICA BIEL: I know, but do you
see people on books very often?

00:09:35.050 --> 00:09:36.950
I don't.

00:09:36.950 --> 00:09:38.037
Are you on a book?

00:09:38.037 --> 00:09:38.870
ALAN SEALES: Me, no.

00:09:38.870 --> 00:09:39.510
JESSICA BIEL: OK, I
thought you would be like,

00:09:39.510 --> 00:09:40.670
well I'm on a book, so.

00:09:40.670 --> 00:09:43.790
ALAN SEALES: Well yeah, I'm
on like six books, books

00:09:43.790 --> 00:09:45.362
about how to interview badly.

00:09:45.362 --> 00:09:47.320
JESSICA BIEL: I think
this is going quite well.

00:09:47.320 --> 00:09:47.860
ALAN SEALES: Oh thank you.

00:09:47.860 --> 00:09:49.170
JESSICA BIEL: I don't know.

00:09:49.170 --> 00:09:50.930
Maybe I'm off.

00:09:50.930 --> 00:09:52.930
ALAN SEALES: We're got a
few holes, so we're OK.

00:09:56.500 --> 00:09:58.760
The series takes place in
Upstate New York, right?

00:09:58.760 --> 00:09:59.100
JESSICA BIEL: Yes.

00:09:59.100 --> 00:10:00.980
ALAN SEALES: Did you film
there, or where did you film

00:10:00.980 --> 00:10:02.105
all the different outsides?

00:10:02.105 --> 00:10:02.850
JESSICA BIEL: No.

00:10:02.850 --> 00:10:07.490
We filmed our pilot in
Charleston, South Carolina,

00:10:07.490 --> 00:10:09.020
which was so cool.

00:10:09.020 --> 00:10:11.600
What a great place
to spend sometime.

00:10:11.600 --> 00:10:15.780
But we did that because we could
sort of fake Upstate New York

00:10:15.780 --> 00:10:16.400
at that time.

00:10:16.400 --> 00:10:18.980
I mean listen, the
foliage is very different,

00:10:18.980 --> 00:10:22.090
but we managed to
fake it a little bit.

00:10:22.090 --> 00:10:24.830
We were dealing with a
time in the year issue.

00:10:24.830 --> 00:10:28.670
And obviously you can see I was
in the water a decent amount.

00:10:28.670 --> 00:10:31.300
And we were really worried about
being Upstate New York in--

00:10:31.300 --> 00:10:32.550
I think it was October.

00:10:32.550 --> 00:10:34.230
It's October we
were filming, so we

00:10:34.230 --> 00:10:37.400
thought that's a little tricky,
little dicey, you never know.

00:10:37.400 --> 00:10:38.795
Could be iced over and frozen.

00:10:38.795 --> 00:10:41.170
It's possible.

00:10:41.170 --> 00:10:42.580
So we filmed the pilot there.

00:10:42.580 --> 00:10:45.310
And then everything else--
we're still filming.

